baseline: Results indicate that mental_health functioning, depression symptoms, and history of mental_health services were associated with suicidal ideation in the hospital; being a parent was a protective factor.
high_intensity: Results indicate that severe mental_health functioning, intense depression symptoms, and a critical history of mental_health services were associated with suicidal ideation in the hospital; being a parent was a protective factor.
low_intensity: Results indicate that mild mental_health functioning, slight depression symptoms, and a basic history of mental_health services were associated with suicidal ideation in the hospital; being a parent was a protective factor.
